  "storyline": "# Storyline\n\n## Context\n\nThe Decision Making & Data Analytics course needed scalable student support and consistent assignment evaluation across a multi-section graduate cohort. Manual grading and feedback workflows created pressure on turnaround time and scoring consistency.\n\n## Workflow\n\nThe role moved from weekly student support sessions into assignment review, NLP-assisted grading automation, faculty calibration, and plagiarism-detection support. The goal was to preserve teaching quality while making evaluation more repeatable.\n\n## Technical Implementation\n\n- **Student support:** ran weekly 3-hour sessions translating probability and analytics concepts into applied examples.\n- **Grading automation:** built a Python, NLP, and BERT workflow supporting evaluation of 400+ assignments (human-in-the-loop).\n- **Scoring consistency:** refined the grading algorithm with 3 faculty members over the term.\n- **Evaluation operations:** supported an estimated ~60% reduction in manual evaluation time and roughly 10 hours/week of faculty time saved.\n- **Plagiarism detection:** improved review support through scoring and similarity-oriented checks.\n\n## Outcomes\n\nThe work supported evaluation across 400+ assignments, an estimated ~60% reduction in grading time, roughly 10 hours/week of faculty time saved, and improved consistency of analytics-course assessment workflows."
